      <ul>
        <li>QB: 1</li>
        <li>RB: 1-4</li>
        <li>WR: 1-4</li>
        <li>TE: 1-4</li>
        <li>PK: 1</li>
        <li>Def: 1</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Lineup Submission</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Lineups are due at "game time" of the player involved.</li>
        <li>Teams that fail to submit a starting lineup, the previous week's lineup will be used.</li>
        <li>Teams must submit a valid lineup each week. A valid lineup consists of no players on a bye or listed as out
          on the NFL injury report, if another option exists on your bench.</li>
        <li>Teams that fail to submit a valid lineup for two consecutive weeks will be considered abandoned.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="salary-caps-contracts">Salary Caps &amp; Contracts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Franchises have a $45 million salary cap that cannot be exceeded.</li>
        <li>Contracts are between 1-5 years and cannot be traded.</li>
        <li>Contracts transfer with the player if traded.</li>
        <li>Players without a contract cannot be traded.</li>
        <li>Rookies are assigned a 5-year contract unless adjusted before the third Sunday in August.</li>
        <li>Teams must have enough cap space for drafted rookies. If not, the player must be signed and then released
          with a 50% cap hit (based on a one-year contract).</li>
        <li>Free agents receive a default 1-year contract. Longer contracts must be submitted within:
          <ul>
            <li>24 hours during the season</li>
            <li>48 hours in the offseason</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Contracts expire on February 15th, reducing by one year. Players with zero years become free agents unless
          tagged.</li>
        <li>Contracts cannot be renegotiated. However, if a player is released and re-signed through free agency, a new
          contract length may be assigned.</li>
      </ul>

