      <h2 id="veteran-extensions">Veteran Extensions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>From now until <strong>February 15, 2028</strong>, each team may extend <strong>one veteran player per
            season</strong>.</li>
        <li>The total contract length after extension may not exceed <strong>6 years</strong>.</li>
        <li>Extension values will follow the same formula used in <strong>Rookie Extensions</strong> (see Rookie
          Extensions section).</li>
        <li>Only <strong>one player per team per season</strong> may be extended under this rule.</li>
        <li><strong>Rookies on 4-year contracts</strong> are not eligible for this type of extension.</li>
        <li>To be eligible, a player must have at least <strong>2 years remaining</strong> on their contract at the time
          of extension.</li>
        <li>This rule applies to <strong>all players equally</strong>. A separate vote will determine how it applies to
          players from the current year's rookie draft.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="rookie-extensions">Rookie Extensions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Rookie Extensions allow teams to add <strong>2 additional years</strong> to a rookie contract.</li>
        <li><strong>Eligibility:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Only rookie contracts that you originally drafted are eligible.</li>
            <li>Players acquired via trade may also be extended, <strong>but only if the extension is applied by
                February 14 at 8:45pm PT in the same league year</strong> they were acquired.</li>
            <li>Extensions may be applied as early as Year 1, but no later than the start of Year 4.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Contract Terms:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>The extension adds two years to the existing contract.</li>
            <li>Extension salary = average of the top 5 salaries at the player's position.</li>
            <li>This average is multiplied by 2 (for two years), then divided by the number of remaining years on
              the contract plus 2.</li>
            <li>The result is added to the player's existing annual salary, and that new total increases by
              <strong>10% per year</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Salary Formula Example:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Player has 2 years remaining on their contract.</li>
            <li>Top 5 positional salary average = $8,500,000</li>
            <li>Extension value = $8.5M × 2 = $17,000,000</li>
            <li>Total contract years (2 remaining + 2 extension) = 4</li>
            <li>17,000,000 ÷ 4 = $4,250,000</li>
            <li>This amount is added to each year, then increased annually by 10%:
              <ul>
                <li>Year 1: $4,250,000</li>
                <li>Year 2: $4,675,000</li>
                <li>Year 3: $5,142,500</li>
                <li>Year 4: $5,656,750</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Link to our <a href="https://www49.myfantasyleague.com/2025/home/13522?MODULE=MESSAGE11">calculator</a> </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Mutual Exclusivity:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>You may <strong>not</strong> apply both a Rookie Extension and a 5th-Year Team Option to the same
              player.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Trade Implications:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Teams acquiring a rookie via trade may extend the player, but must do so before <strong>February 14
                at 8:45pm PT</strong>.</li>
            <li>After that deadline, rookie contracts acquired via trade become <strong>ineligible for
                extension</strong>.</li>
            <li>Players acquired via draft-day trades (any trade involving rookies while the draft is still going
              on) remain fully eligible for extension.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="first-round-team-option">First-Round Team Option</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>All 1st-round draft picks are signed to a 4-year rookie contract with a <strong>5th-year team option</strong>.</li>
        <li><strong>Team Option Terms:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>The 5th-year salary is based on the <strong>average of the top 10 salaries</strong> at the player's position.</li>
            <li>This team option provides one additional contract year, bringing the maximum length to 5 years.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Decision Deadline:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>The team option must be exercised <strong>before the player's 4th year begins</strong>.</li>
            <li>If the option is not declared by that time, the player will enter their final year under the rookie contract and become a free agent afterward unless franchise tagged.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Mutual Exclusivity:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>You may <strong>not</strong> use both a rookie extension and the 5th-year team option on the same player.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <blockquote class="fine-print">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Team options are only available for players selected in the 1st round of the rookie draft from 2026 onward.
      </blockquote>

      <h2 id="compensatory-picks">Compensatory Picks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>If a team chooses <strong>not to extend a drafted player</strong> and the player signs with another team in free agency, the original team may receive a <strong>3rd-round compensatory pick</strong>.</li>
        <li><strong>Eligibility Criteria:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>The player must have been originally drafted by the team.</li>
            <li>The player must <strong>sign via auction before May 1 at 8:45pm PT</strong>.</li>
            <li>No compensatory pick will be awarded for signings that occur after this deadline.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Compensatory Pick Rules:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Only one compensatory pick is awarded per player.</li>
            <li>Each owner is responsible for <strong>tracking and posting</strong> eligible compensatory picks before the rookie draft begins.</li>
            <li>Compensatory picks are awarded at the end of the 3rd round (e.g., 3.17, 3.18).</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Compensatory Pick Order:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>The order of compensatory picks will follow the base draft order for that season.</li>
            <li>If multiple teams are awarded more than one compensatory pick, all teams will first receive their <strong>first compensatory pick</strong> in base draft order.</li>
            <li>The process will then repeat to award all <strong>second compensatory picks</strong> in the same order, and so on, until all compensatory picks have been distributed.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <blockquote class="fine-print">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Compensatory picks are only available for players drafted in the 2026 draft and beyond. Signings that occur outside of the official free agency auction process are not eligible.
      </blockquote>

      <h2 id="free-agent-bidding">Free Agent Bidding</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>FA bidding starts on the <strong>3rd Thursday in March (15th–21st)</strong> and ends the
          <strong>Wednesday</strong> before the NFL season opener.
        </li>
        <li>No new auctions after the <strong>3rd Sunday in August</strong> (or three weeks before the first Sunday
          game, whichever is later) at 8:45 PM PT.</li>
        <li>Two blind bid periods occur between the 3rd Sunday in August and the start of the NFL season.</li>
        <li>FA bidding follows an eBay-style auction format.</li>
        <li>Starting bid: $425,000 | Minimum bid increase: $25,000.</li>
        <li>To bid, teams must:
          <ul>
            <li>Have at least $425,000 in cap space.</li>
            <li>Increase bids by at least $25,00*.</li>
            <li>Have an open roster spot.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>After <strong>36 hours without a new bid</strong>, the highest bidder wins.</li>
        <li>FA signings receive a <strong>default 1-year contract</strong>. Longer contracts must be
          submitted<strong>within 48 hours</strong> via transaction comments or the league message board.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="rookie-draft">Rookie Draft</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The 3-round rookie draft occurs the<strong>Sunday after the NFL Draft</strong>.</li>
        <li>Only rookies in the <strong>MFL database</strong> are eligible.</li>
        <li>Each pick has a <strong>12-hour timer</strong>, paused from <strong>12 AM to 4 AM PT</strong>.</li>
        <li>Draft order follows the <strong>reverse order of the prior season's record</strong>, with ties broken
          by <strong>All-Play record</strong>.</li>
        <li><strong>First two rounds are mandatory</strong>; teams must select a player.</li>
        <li><strong>Third-round picks are optional</strong> (owners may pass).</li>
        <li>Players from the <strong>NFL Supplemental Draft and international rookies</strong> enter free agency.</li>
        <li><strong>Toilet Bowl Challenge awards compensatory picks</strong>: 1.17, 2.17, 2.18.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="in-season-free-agent-blind-bidding-process">In-Season Free Agent Blind Bidding Process</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>The <strong>In-Season FA period</strong> runs from <strong>Week 1 through Week 17</strong>.</li>
        <li>Free agents are acquired through:
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Blind Bidding:</strong> Sunday <strong>10 PM PT – Wednesday 7 PM PT</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>First-Come, First-Served (FCFS):</strong> Wednesday <strong>7 PM PT – Sunday 10 AM
                PT</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>FCFS Rules:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Salary = <strong>$425,000 minimum</strong>.</li>
            <li>Longer contracts must be declared within <strong>24 hours</strong> or <strong>before the player's
                game starts</strong>.</li>
            <li><strong>Players are locked</strong> once their game begins.</li>
            <li><strong>Dropped players</strong> are locked until <strong>Sunday at 10:15 AM PT</strong> and must
              first go through a bid period.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Blind Bidding Budget:</strong> Equals <strong>remaining salary cap space</strong>.</li>
        <li>All FA signings default to <strong>1-year contracts</strong> unless extended within <strong>24
            hours</strong> via transaction comments or the league message board.</li>
        <li>Players dropped <strong>after Week 14 (Sunday 1 PM ET / 10 AM PT)</strong>:
          <ul>
            <li>Can only be signed for <strong>one year</strong>.</li>
            <li>Cannot be <strong>tagged</strong>.</li>
            <li>Becomes <strong>free agents at season's end</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

