      <h2 id="playoff-structure">Playoff Structure</h2>
      The entire league will be seeded 1-16 in reverse order of their regular season standings. The tiebreakers referenced
      above will be used to break any and all ties. The entire
      league will be broken up into 3 groups:
      <p><strong>League Championships</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>The 4 division winners and 3 wildcard teams will make the playoffs.</li>
        <li>The four division champions are seeded 1 through 4 based on their regular season won-lost-tied record.</li>
        <li>Three wild card qualifiers (those non-division champions with the conference's best winning percentages),
          are seeded 5, 6 and 7.</li>
        <li>The division winner with the best regular season record will be seeded #1 and receive a first round bye.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Play-in Game</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>The 8th seed will play the 9th seed.</li>
        <li>The winner will play the highest seeded team to loose in the first round of the League Championships</li>
        <li>The loser will play the loser of the 12th seed vs the 13 seed in the Toilet Bowl Challenge.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Toilet Bowl Challenge</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>The remaining 7 seeds will face off in the Toilet Bowl Challenge</li>
        <li>The 16th seed will receive a first round bye</li>
        <li>Unlike the League Championships the Toilet Bowl Challenge is not reseeded after each round.</li>
      </ul>
